<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="313" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,332,357]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Distribution.</emphasis>
From northern Africa (
<collectingCountry box="[635,741,332,356]" name="Morocco" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[757,843,332,357]" name="Tunisia" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[859,928,332,356]" name="Egypt" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Egypt</collectingCountry>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[981,1058,332,357]" name="Jordan" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Jordan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1075,1137,332,357]" name="Israel" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Israel</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1202,1303,332,357]" name="Palestine" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Palestine</collectingCountry>
and to the Arabian Peninsula (
<collectingCountry box="[371,624,367,392]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,404,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Pollen hosts.</emphasis>
Polylectic with a strong preference for 
<taxonomicName box="[840,989,404,429]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Brassicaceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<number box="[1005,1019,404,428]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="8.0">8</number>
of 
<number box="[1068,1096,404,428]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="10.0">10</number>
pollen loads (
<number box="[1273,1287,404,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="6.0">6</number>
localities, 
<number box="[1422,1436,404,428]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="3.0">3</number>
countries) consisted of 
<taxonomicName box="[421,566,439,464]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Brassicaceae</taxonomicName>
pollen, one load each exclusively contained pollen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1206,1385,439,464]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Zygophyllaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygophyllales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Zygophyllaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,285,476,501]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Resedaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Capparales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Resedaceae</taxonomicName>
, respectively. Males and females of 
<taxonomicName box="[715,862,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jordanica">
<emphasis box="[715,862,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">H. jordanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were observed on the small white flowers of an unknown annual 
<taxonomicName box="[366,511,511,536]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Brassicaceae</taxonomicName>
species in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[781,864,511,536]" name="Tunisia" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
(C. Sedivy, C. Praz and A. Müller, personal observation). Label records of collected specimens also indicate that annual 
<taxonomicName box="[1024,1169,548,573]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Brassicaceae</taxonomicName>
are exploited as pollen hosts, e.g. 
<taxonomicName box="[270,457,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Diplotaxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harra">
<emphasis box="[270,457,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Diplotaxis harra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[512,709,585,608]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Erucaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rostrata">
<emphasis box="[512,709,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Erucaria rostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,645]" box="[199,514,620,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
